{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3454229,"name":"Tiago Rodrigues de Moraes Godoy","username":"TiagoGodoy","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/tiagogodoy/{size}/238115_2.png","created_at":"2024-12-03T18:48:51.619Z","cooked":"<p>My team has used MAX Swerve since last season and we have always had a problem while moving forward with the Swerve. When we just move it forward, the robot turns too, not being a straight translation and it’s so visible. We tried to calibrate it a lot of times. Does anyone know what can be our problem?</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":16,"updated_at":"2024-12-03T18:48:51.619Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":69,"reads":164,"readers_count":163,"score":392.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":475936,"topic_slug":"max-swerve-turning-while-moving-forward-issue","display_username":"Tiago Rodrigues de Moraes Godoy","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":67842,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/max-swerve-turning-while-moving-forward-issue/475936/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3454230,"name":"","username":"AvocadoPeel","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/avocadopeel/{size}/232401_2.png","created_at":"2024-12-03T18:54:08.093Z","cooked":"<p>there are many things that could cause this, the main 3 that come to mind: the chassis frame isnt perfectly square, the modules absolute offsets are slightly misaligned, the desired and achieved wheel speeds dont match.</p>
<p>try plotting the module setpoints and actual speeds and see if theres a difference, is an easy place to start.</p>
<p>another solution (after trying to find he route cause) is making the swerve snap to angle with the gyro when theres no turning input</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":16,"updated_at":"2024-12-03T18:54:08.093Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":162,"readers_count":161,"score":52.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":475936,"topic_slug":"max-swerve-turning-while-moving-forward-issue","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":61239,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/max-swerve-turning-while-moving-forward-issue/475936/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3454235,"name":"","username":"nstrike","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/nstrike/{size}/167038_2.png","created_at":"2024-12-03T19:04:33.635Z","cooked":"<p>There are alot of optimizations that go into this one action, i would recommend YAGSL after the <code>beta</code> release today because they are built in and by far the easiest option.</p>
